Annotation.note:
This is the famous family of systems with $C_n$ symmetry first
considered by Arnborg, Bj\&quot;ork, and Fr\&quot;oberg. For a survey see the
paper by Backelin/Fr\&quot;oberg in the proceedings of ISSAC'91.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple
cyclic:=proc(n) 
  local i,j,k,polys,vars;
  vars:=[seq(x.i,i=1..n)];
  polys:=[mul(x.i,i=1..n)-1,
  seq(add(mul(x.((k mod n)+1), k=j..(j+i)), j=0..(n-1)), i=0..n-2)];
end;
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
discrete symmetries
\end{keywords}
